Both sensitivity analyses use a lower cutoff of $\mu_\star^{(i)} > 1$~GeV to ensure four-loop QCD running is reliable. To verify that this cutoff is not coupling the sample to the comparison observable, we re-run the perturbation sensitivity analysis under three alternative cutoffs:
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{lc}
\toprule
$\mu_\text{min}$ & Preservation rate \\
\midrule
$0.7$~GeV (extrapolated; running not strictly trusted) & $0.50\%$ \\
$1.0$~GeV (baseline) & $0.58\%$ \\
